---
title: Pub-Style Shepherd’s Pie with White Cheddar & Thyme Mashed Potatoes
description: No matter the weather, we firmly believe that there’s nothing better than homey, comforting classics that warm you from the inside out. If you wholeheartedly agree, look no further! Enter: our chefs’ ode to the classic shepherd’s pie. The base is a rich, tomatoey beef filling chock-full of fresh veggies and herbs. On top, swoops of creamy, thyme-flecked mashed potatoes are sprinkled with sharp white cheddar, then broiled to create an irresistibly cheesy crust. It all bakes up in one dish, making it easy as... well, you know!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61f982bf055a054a23694946-dcaae436.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pub-style-shepherds-pie-61f982bf055a054a23694946-6b304c21.pdf
servings: 2
cuisine: European
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pub-style-shepherds-pie-61f982bf055a054a23694946
time required: 50 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 870 kcal
  fat: 53 g
  saturated fat: 25 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1360 mg
---

Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Strip @thyme{¼%ounce}(leaves stripped and roughly chopped) from stems. Trim, peel, and halve @carrot{3%ounce}(trimmed and sliced crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons). Finely dice @celery{2.5%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely chop @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped).

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain and return potatoes to pot.

Mash potatoes with @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, 1 tsp chopped thyme, and @butter{2%tablespoon} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of water as needed. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrot; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add celery, onion, and a large drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until veggies are just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. 

> If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and 2 tsp chopped thyme; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce} to pan with veggies and season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @flour{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until thoroughly combined, ~{1%minute}.

Add half the @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce} and @water{½%cup} into pan with beef mixture.

> For 4 servings, use all the crushed tomatoes and ¾ cup water.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{2} and bring to a boil. Cook until mixture is very thick, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.

Top beef filling with an even layer of mashed potatoes, leaving a gap around edge of pan. Evenly sprinkle with @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}.

Broil until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Serve directly from pan.